x4freetext: For short-lived fission products, nitrate solutions
of 241Pu (~ 2 ug) sealed in polypropylene tubes were
irradiated in the reactor CIRUS for 60 sec to 10 min
using pneumatic carrier facility at a flux of 5 x
targets of 241Pu (~ 25 ug) covered with 0.025 mm thick
aluminum foils were irradiated in the reactor APSARA
for 10 min to 7 h at a flux of 1.2 x 10**12 n/cm2/sec
80 cm3 detector connected to a PC based 4096
The resolution of the detector system was 2.0 keV at
number of target atoms, neutron flux and flux
dead time of the detector system (<10%)
